{# Port-wiring snippet for Python / FastAPI backends.

Renders a port import + adapter-factory block intended for the
``FORGE:APP_POST_CONFIGURE`` anchor in ``src/app/core/container.py``
(the canonical site where queue_port + every Pillar D port wires
its concrete adapter). The same anchor is reused for
``Depends(get_<port>)`` style FastAPI dependency overrides — the
factory line emits whatever the spec author passes in
``service_factory``, so a Depends-style wire is a one-line change
on the caller side.

Spec context (``port``) — every field is required:
  - name              — snake_case identifier (e.g. ``llm``, ``queue``)
  - interface_path    — module path of the Port protocol; the macro
                        strips ``.py`` and converts slashes to dots
                        (``app/ports/llm.py`` → ``app.ports.llm``)
  - adapter_imports   — tuple of dotted modules to import (the
                        adapter implementations to wire). Each becomes
                        one ``import`` line; if the entry contains a
                        space (``"X from Y"`` shape) it's emitted as
                        a ``from … import …``.
  - service_factory   — the wiring statement. Verbatim — typically
                        an assignment like
                        ``_<port>_adapter = <Adapter>(<config>)`` or
                        a ``Depends(get_<port>)`` override. Multiline
                        OK; the macro preserves indentation.
#}
{%- macro snippet(port) -%}
# Port: {{ port.name }}
from {{ port.interface_path
            | replace('/', '.')
            | replace('.py', '') }} import *  # noqa: F401,F403 — port contract import
{% for imp in port.adapter_imports -%}
{% if ' from ' in imp -%}
{# Shape: ``Adapter from module.path`` → ``from module.path import Adapter`` #}
from {{ imp.split(' from ', 1)[1] }} import {{ imp.split(' from ', 1)[0] }}
{%- else -%}
import {{ imp }}
{%- endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{{ port.service_factory }}
{%- endmacro %}
